{"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["**Notebook 2: Exploratory Data Analysis**\n","\n","**1.Introduction**\n","\n","Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) is performed to understand patterns, relationships, and distributions in the dataset. Both graphical and non-graphical methods are used."],"metadata":{"id":"HWMmHQgGdqHx"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","import seaborn as sns"],"metadata":{"id":"CUlIfvBIeOxo"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["**2.Non-Graphical Analysis**\n","\n","Analysis 1: Central Tendency\n","\n","The first analysis focuses on understanding the central tendency of the marks variable. Measures such as mean, median, and mode are calculated to determine the average performance of students. When the mean and median values are close to each other, it indicates that the data distribution is approximately symmetric.\n","\n","From this analysis, it is observed that the marks are fairly evenly distributed, suggesting that there is no extreme skewness in student performance.\n","\n","Analysis 2: Correlation Analysis\n","\n","The second analysis examines the relationships between multiple variables using correlation coefficients. This multivariate analysis helps in identifying how strongly variables such as study hours and attendance are related to marks.\n","\n","The results indicate a strong positive correlation between study hours and marks, implying that students who study more tend to score higher. Attendance also shows a moderate positive relationship with marks, suggesting that regular class participation contributes to better performance.\n","\n","\n","**3.Graphical Analysis**\n","\n","Analysis 3: Histogram\n","\n","A histogram is used to visualize the distribution of marks. This univariate graphical method helps in understanding the frequency distribution of the data.\n","\n","The histogram reveals a bell-shaped curve, indicating that the data follows an approximately normal distribution. This suggests that most students score around the average, with fewer students achieving extremely high or low marks.\n","\n","**Analysis 4: Scatter Plot**\n","\n","A scatter plot is used to analyze the relationship between study hours and marks. This multivariate graphical technique helps in identifying trends and patterns.\n","\n","The plot shows a clear upward trend, indicating a positive relationship between the two variables. This confirms that increased study time generally leads to improved academic performance."],"metadata":{"id":"s_tAJXd1eauk"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import pandas as pd\n","\n","try:\n","    df = pd.read_csv(\"student_performance.csv\", encoding='latin-1')\n","\n","    # Check if column exists\n","    if 'marks' in df.columns:\n","\n","        # Convert to numeric (safe handling)\n","        df['marks'] = pd.to_numeric(df['marks'], errors='coerce')\n","\n","        # Mean\n","        print(\"Mean of marks:\", df['marks'].mean())\n","\n","        # Median\n","        print(\"Median of marks:\", df['marks'].median())\n","\n","        # Mode\n","        print(\"Mode of marks:\")\n","        print(df['marks'].mode())\n","\n","    else:\n","        print(\"Error: 'marks' column not found in dataset.\")\n","\n","except FileNotFoundError:\n","    print(\"Error: File not found. Please upload 'student_performance.csv'.\")\n","\n","except Exception as e:\n","    print(\"Error:\", e)"],"metadata":{"id":"vnTGMsEafETd","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776329467659,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":12,"user":{"displayName":"","userId":""}},"outputId":"4fa61832-557b-4892-eead-defcb0b210c0","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"}},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Error: File not found. Please upload 'student_performance.csv'.\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import pandas as pd\n","\n","try:\n","    df = pd.read_csv(\"student_performance.csv\", encoding='latin-1')\n","\n","    # Check required columns\n","    required_cols = ['study_hours', 'attendance', 'marks']\n","\n","    if all(col in df.columns for col in required_cols):\n","\n","        # Convert to numeric (safe handling)\n","        for col in required_cols:\n","            df[col] = pd.to_numeric(df[col], errors='coerce')\n","\n","        # Correlation matrix\n","        print(df[required_cols].corr())\n","\n","    else:\n","        print(\"Error: One or more required columns not found.\")\n","\n","except FileNotFoundError:\n","    print(\"Error: File not found. Please upload dataset.\")\n","\n","except Exception as e:\n","    print(\"Error:\", e)"],"metadata":{"id":"1fSKpHwafQ8U","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776329592879,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":145,"user":{"displayName":"","userId":""}},"outputId":"70571ee3-e504-4cfd-9af1-c06ed10cb9df","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"}},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Error: File not found. Please upload dataset.\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import pandas as pd\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","\n","try:\n","    df = pd.read_csv(\"student_performance.csv\", encoding='latin-1')\n","\n","    if 'marks' in df.columns:\n","\n","        # Convert to numeric safely\n","        df['marks'] = pd.to_numeric(df['marks'], errors='coerce')\n","        df = df.dropna(subset=['marks'])\n","\n","        # Histogram\n","        plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))\n","        plt.hist(df['marks'], bins=15, color='blue', edgecolor='black')\n","\n","        plt.title(\"Marks Distribution\")\n","        plt.xlabel(\"Marks\")\n","        plt.ylabel(\"Frequency\")\n","\n","        plt.show()\n","\n","    else:\n","        print(\"Error: 'marks' column not found.\")\n","\n","except FileNotFoundError:\n","    print(\"Error: File not found. Please upload dataset.\")\n","\n","except Exception as e:\n","    print(\"Error:\", e)"],"metadata":{"id":"aRXXp7MXgVR_","executionInfo"